label.value: larval abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'td1

value.value: Tracheal associated multidendritic neuron of the ventral' cluster of segments A1-6 found ventral to v'td2 (Qian et al., 2018). Like other neurons of this cluster, it follows the SNa branch of the segmental nerve (Williams and Shepherd, 1999). After entering the ventral nerve cord, it projects anteriorly, reaching the subesophageal zone (Qian et al., 2018). It expresses chemosensory receptors (Qian et al., 2018).

definition.value: Sometimes both v'td neurons in a hemisegment are collectively referred to as v'td2, as in Williams and Shepherd (1999).

label.value: larval abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'td2

value.value: Tracheal associated multidendritic neuron of the ventral' cluster of segments A1-7 (Qian et al., 2018). In A1-6 it is located dorsal to v'td1, in A7 it is the only type of ventral tracheal dendrite neuron (Qian et al., 2018). Like other neurons of this cluster, it follows the SNa branch of the segmental nerve (Williams and Shepherd, 1999). After entering the ventral nerve cord, it projects anteriorly, with neurons of more anterior segments (A1-A3) reaching the subesophageal zone and more posterior neurons terminating in the vicinity of the metathoracic neuromere (Qian et al., 2018). It expresses gustatory receptors, indicating that it may be chemosensory (Qian et al., 2018).

definition.value: Sometimes both v'td neurons in a hemisegment are collectively referred to as v'td2, as in Williams and Shepherd (1999).

label.value: abdominal ventral bipolar dendrite neuron vbd

value.value: Bipolar dendrite neuron with its soma in the ventral sensory cluster of a larval abdominal segment, close to vdaA-D (Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005). It emits two dendritic branches along the anterior posterior axis (Bodmer and Jan, 1987; Orgogozo and Grueber, 2005). It is a proprioceptor neuron (Heckscher et al., 2015). It has strong outputs to the A08e3 local neuron, Jaam2 and A02b (Heckscher et al., 2015; Schneider-Mizell et al., 2016). It is cholinergic (Heckman and Doe, 2022).

definition.value: The number of identified output synapses to Jaam2 was 32/21 (L/R) and to A08e3 was 15/9 (Heckscher et al., 2015). It is still not known if the pattern of connections in A1 is replicated in the other abdominal segments (Heckscher et al., 2015). The number of output synapses in Schneider-Mizell et al. (2016) was the estimated from the publication figures (number in brackets left/right where available; ipsi- and contralateral connections separated by comma): to A02b (15, 8/15, 10).

Unpaired nerve that exits the dorsal part of an abdominal neuromere (Santos et al., 2006). There is no equivalent nerve in thoracic segments (Santos et al., 2006).

Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 1 (Santos et al., 2006). It has a large swelling, corresponding to an abdominal neurohemal organ. It does not give rise to transverse nerves in the first instar (Gorczyca et al., 1994), but does branch relatively proximally to produce these nerves in the third instar (Santos et al., 2006).

Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 2 (Santos et al., 2006). It has a slightly smaller swelling than the A1 nerve, corresponding to an abdominal neurohemal organ, and it bifurcates relatively proximally to give rise to two transverse nerves (Santos et al., 2006).

Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 3 (Santos et al., 2006). It has a smaller swelling than the two anterior nerves, corresponding to an abdominal neurohemal organ, and it bifurcates relatively proximally to give rise to two transverse nerves (Santos et al., 2006).

Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 3 (Santos et al., 2006). It does not possess a swelling at its base (Santos et al., 2006), but still bifurcates relatively proximally to form two transverse nerves (Gorczyca et al., 1994).
